{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5b11e37d-292b-49eb-9f64-13b9f85de5b4","content":"With MSTest 3.8.2, you can inject `TestContext` via the constructor and use `[TestInitialize]` (which supports `async Task`) for async setup. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext + sync init\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        _service = new MyService();\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.ConnectAsync();\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Test initialized\");\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.DisconnectAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task MyTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test\");\n        var result = await _service.DoWorkAsync();\n        Assert.IsNotNull(result);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — receives `TestContext` via DI; use for synchronous setup.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — can return `async Task`; use for async per-test setup.\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — available for one-time async class-level setup (static method).\n- Avoid the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern; constructor injection is the modern replacement.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"492bf68a-7401-4596-8923-ccf81afbfb58","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has MSTest 3.8.2 which supports constructor injection for TestContext. Let me provide the recommended modern MSTest pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, you can inject `TestContext` via the constructor. For async initialization, you implement `IAsyncInitialization` or use `[TestInitialize]` with an async method. Let me give a clear, accurate answer.\n\nActually, in modern MSTest (v3), the recommended approach is:\n1. Constructor injection for `TestContext` (instead of the old property-based approach)\n2. `[TestInitialize]` for synchronous per-test setup\n\n\n3. `[TestInitialize]` can also be async for per-test async setup\n4. `[ClassInitialize]` handles one-time class-level initialization\n\nNow I'll show a concrete example of how to use these patterns together.","outputTokens":583,"requestId":"603A:1521A3:244B5C2:26EFB02:6A0311E6"},"id":"113298f5-6f32-4126-8804-1973defc81a0","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:41:39.946Z","parentId":"fda0a02f-2360-45d6-8e0a-d607a99771f4"}
